&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/PH/PREVENTIONWELLNESS/Pages/Psilocybin-Administrative-Rules.aspx" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;Rules Advisory Committees&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(RACs) are an important process that allow members of the public an opportunity to provide input on proposed administrative rules before they become effective. RACs are comprised of individuals who have subject matter expertise and members of the public who are likely to be affected by the proposed rules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The RAC process is designed to include a diversity of opinions and viewpoints. Although RACs evaluate fiscal and racial impact of the proposed rules and make recommendations, Oregon Health Authority (OHA) retains decision making authority.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All community members will be invited to provide comments on the proposed rules during the public comment period scheduled from Dec. 1 to Dec. 22, 2025. Information about the public comment period is available on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.oregon.gov/oha/PH/PREVENTIONWELLNESS/Pages/Psilocybin-Administrative-Rules.aspx" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;Oregon Psilocybin Services Administrative Rules&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;webpage and will be sent out to the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://public.govdelivery.com/accounts/ORHA/signup/37680" style="text-size-adjust: 100%; color: rgb(6, 66, 118);"&gt;OPS mailing list&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;later this year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;###&lt;/p&gt;

